<HEADLINE> `Wild Wild West' Tops at Box Office / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ``Wild Wild West'' opened with $36.4 million  
to win the four-day Fourth of July holiday box office contest, 
while ``South Park: Bigger, Longer and Uncut'' made its debut with 
a respectable $14.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The top 20 movies at North American theaters Friday through  
Monday, followed by distributing studio, gross, number of theater 
locations, average receipts per location, total gross and number of 
weeks in release, as compiled Tuesday by Exhibitor Relations Co. 
Inc. and ACNielsen EDI Inc.: 
</P>
<P>
	1. ``Wild Wild West,'' Warner Bros., $36.4 million, 3,342  
locations, $10,902 average, $49.7 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	2. ``Big Daddy,'' Sony, $26.8 million, 3,121 locations, $8,597  
average, $90.5 million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	3. ``Tarzan,'' Disney, $19.3 million, 3,103 locations, $6,234  
average, $111.1 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	4. ``South Park: Bigger, Longer and Uncut,'' Paramount, $14.8  
million, 2,128 locations, $6,943 average, $23.1 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	5. ``The General's Daughter,'' Paramount, $14.2 million, 2,858  
locations, $4,971 average, $67.4 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	6. ``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace,'' 20th Century  
Fox, $13.3 million, 2,628 locations, $5,058 average, $373.2 
million, seven weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	7. ``Austin Powers: The Spy Who Shagged Me,'' New Line, $12.1  
million, 3,091 locations, $3,900 average, $171.4 million, four 
weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	8. ``Summer of Sam,'' Disney, $8 million, 1,536 locations,  
$5,203 average, $8 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	9. ``Notting Hill,'' Universal, $5.5 million, 1,944 locations,  
$2,830 average, $98.3 million, six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	10. ``An Ideal Husband,'' Miramax, $3.6 million, 602 sites,  
$6,043 average, $5.7 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	11. ``The Mummy,'' Universal, $1.3 million, 992 locations,  
$1,280 average, $148.3 million, nine weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	12. ``The Red Violin,'' Lions Gate, $882,894, 261 locations,  
$3,383 average, $4.6 million, four weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	13. ``Instinct,'' Disney, $807,542, 832 locations, $971 average,  
$32.2 million, five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	14. ``Shakespeare in Love,'' Miramax, $782,388, 618 locations,  
$1,266 average, $98.7 million, 30 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	15. ``Tea With Mussolini,'' MGM, $755,594, 284 locations, $2,661  
average, $10.8 million, eight weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	16. ``The Matrix,'' Warner Bros., $608,249, 747 locations, $814  
average, $166.8 million, 14 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	17. ``Entrapment,'' 20th Century Fox, $522,877, 553 locations,  
$946 average, $84.4 million, 10 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	18. ``Run Lola Run,'' Sony Pictures Classics, $498,037, 45  
locations, $11,067 average, $1.1 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	19. ``Buena Vista Social Club,'' Artisan, $386,222, 50  
locations, $7,724 average, $1.5 million, five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	20. ``Never Been Kissed,'' 20th Century Fox, $363,193, 469  
locations, $774 average, $53.8 million, 13 weeks. 
  	   	
</P>
