<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brown To Plead Innocent to 2 Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Jim Brown, a Hall of Fame football player and  
actor, will plead innocent Friday to two misdemeanor charges for 
allegedly threatening to kill his wife and breaking her car windows 
with a shovel, according to his lawyer. 
</P>
<P>
	The former Cleveland Browns star faces one count of making a  
terrorist threat and one count of vandalism. He could receive up to 
18 months in jail and a $2,000 fine if convicted on both counts. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown, 63, his lawyer and his 25-year-old wife, Monique, were in  
court Tuesday and told reporters afterward the case had been 
overblown. 
</P>
<P>
	``The point we tried to make was that Monique was never harmed  
in any way,'' said William Graysen, a Century City criminal defense 
lawyer. ``Since the O.J. Simpson case, if there's a family argument 
and police are called, someone will get arrested. We want everyone 
to know it's not a violence case, it's a threat case.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Brown was arrested June 15 at the couple's Hollywood Hills home  
after his wife of two years reported the alleged incident. He was 
booked at the Hollywood station and posted $50,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Brown later held an impromptu news conference outside their  
home and denied that threats were made against her. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown retired from pro football in 1966 with many NFL rushing  
and scoring records. He also has appeared in several Hollywood 
films, notably ``The Dirty Dozen.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
