<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gulfstream Park To Sell to MI </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HALLANDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Gulfstream Park agreed Tuesday to sell  
the track to MI Ventures Inc. for $95 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The announcement was made in a news release by Gulfstream, where  
the Breeders' Cup will be held Nov. 5-7. The 2000 meeting will run 
from Jan. 3 through March 16. 
</P>
<P>
	Gulfstream has been owned by Gulfstream Holdings Inc. of  
Illinois, a subsidiary of Orient Corp. and Higashi Nihon House Co. 
of Japan, for eight years. 
</P>
<P>
	Ventures is Magna International Inc.'s non-automotive group.  
</P>
<P>
	``We are confident Ventures will further strengthen Gulfstream's  
ranking as Florida's No. 1 thoroughbred track and one of the 
industry's national leaders,'' said Akihiro Terada, Orient's 
spokesman at Gulfstream Park. 
</P>
<P>
	The transaction is expected to close in the third quarter of  
1999. 
</P>
<P>
	In January, Churchill Downs signed an agreement to purchase  
Calder Race Course in Miami for $86 million. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
