<HEADLINE> Indians Send Whiten, Tam to Buffalo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Mark Whiten's return to the Cleveland Indians  
didn't last long. 
</P>
<P>
	Whiten was optioned to Buffalo of the Triple-A International  
League on Tuesday along with right-handed pitcher Jeff Tam. The 
Indians recalled outfielders Jacob Cruz and Alex Ramirez. 
</P>
<P>
	Whiten, who broke his right foot during spring training in  
February, was activated from the 60-day disabled list on June 23. 
But the outfielder went just 4-for-25 in eight games for the 
Indians. 
</P>
<P>
	Tam appeared for Cleveland for the first time in Sunday's 10-9  
loss to the Kansas City Royals. He lasted just a third of an inning 
and gave up three runs. 
</P>
<P>
	Cruz and Ramirez both hit better than .300 for Cleveland in  
short stints with the Indians earlier this year. 
  	   	
</P>
