<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-06 16:40:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Laments Midwest Shootings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST ST. LOUIS, Ill. (AP) -- President Clinton urged all  
Americans to ``rid our hearts of hatred, immediately'' in response 
to the deadly drive-by shootings in Illinois and Indiana apparently 
carried out by a white supremacist. 
</P>
<P>
	Visiting here Tuesday as part of his national poverty tour, the  
president said the shootings were driven by ``blind racial hatred 
against anybody who didn't happen to be white,'' and underscored 
the need for the United States to strengthen its hate crimes laws 
and continue striving for racial harmony. 
</P>
<P>
	``We still have work to do here at home,'' Clinton told a crowd  
of about 1,000 outside a Walgreen's drug store. ``We must search 
the hearts of our citizens and search the strength of our 
communities. The Congress should pass the hate crimes legislation, 
but we should rid our hearts our hatred, immediately.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Eleven people were shot during the weekend shooting spree, all  
of them either Jews, blacks or Asians. Two people were killed and 
nine wounded. Benjamin Nathaniel Smith, 21, shot and killed himself 
during a struggle with police Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Clinton noted that the shootings took place during the July  
Fourth holiday weekend, as Americans were honoring the founding of 
their democracy. ``That action was a rebuke to the very ideals that 
got us started,'' Clinton said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
