<HEADLINE> Orioles May Pick Up Ripken Option </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Baltimore Orioles will pick up a $6.3  
million option to keep third baseman Cal Ripken next year, sources 
told The (Baltimore) Sun. 
</P>
<P>
	The move, which was expected, will be announced during a  
three-game homestand this week against the Toronto Blue Jays, 
according to the paper. 
</P>
<P>
	Ripken is headed to his 17th All-Star game. He rejuvenated his  
production after his first career stint on the disabled list this 
year, as he closes in on 400 career homers and 3,000 career hits. 
He is batting .310 with 11 home runs and 34 RBIs, and has 395 
homers and 2,943 hits for his career. 
</P>
<P>
	His durability allowed him to play in a record-setting 2,632  
consecutive games, a streak he ended last year. But Ripken, who 
turns 39 next month, said during spring training he would allow his 
performance to dictate whether he would return. 
</P>
<P>
	``Without question, it's going to happen. It's a given,'' a  
source told The Sun. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
