<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Elf Aquitaine, up 16 1/16 at 90 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	France's largest oil company, Total Fina SA, launched a $43  
billion hostile takeover bid Monday for rival Elf Aquitaine. If 
successful, the combined oil company would be the world's 
fourth-largest in terms of market share. 

</P>
<P>
 *General Motors Corp., up 3 3/8 at 72    	
</P>
<P>
	In an article published this week in Barron's, Sanford Bernstein  
analyst Gary Lapidus outlined an aggressive strategy for GM to more 
than double its stock price and triple its per-share earnings by 
cutting the number of shares outstanding. 

</P>
<P>
 *DBT Online, down 3 9/16 at 29 5/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Miami Herald reported last weekend that DBT, a provider of  
online investigative services, lost contracts with the FBI and U.S. 
Drug Enforcement Administration because its founder was once 
suspected of having ties to drug smugglers. 

</P>
<P>
 *BOC Group PLC, up 3 11/16 at 43 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	BOC, a British maker of industrial gases, has revived talks with  
U.S. company Air Products &AMP; Chemicals Inc. The move could lead to a 
bidding war for BOC, which is also coveted by France's Air Liquide 
SA. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Dr. Koop.com, up 12 3/4 at 36 3/8  
</P>
<P>
 *America Online Inc., up 7 3/8 at 122 5/8 on the NYSE 
</P>
<P>
	The health information Web site will pay $89 million over four  
years to become the lead health content provider to America Online. 
Meanwhile, AOL will receive warrants to purchase a stake in 
Drkoop.com. 

</P>
<P>
 *Books-A-Million, up 2 9/16 at 14 5/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Web site JagNotes.com published a rumor that Books-A-Million,  
the nation's third-largest book retailer, may be acquired by 
Borders, the second-largest U.S. bookseller. 

</P>
<P>
 *General Nutrition Companies Inc., up 1 11/16 at 24 9/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Dutch food maker Royal Numico is acquiring GNC, a leading  
producer of vitamins and other nutritional supplements, for $1.75 
billion in cash. Royal Numico will also assume roughly $760 million 
in debt. 

</P>
<P>
 *Dset Corp., down 3 3/8 at 10 7/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Dset, a telecommunications software maker, estimates  
second-quarter earnings between 4 cents and 6 cents a share. 
Analysts surveyed by First Call Corp. had expected Dset to earn 11 
cents per share. 


  	   	
</P>
