<HEADLINE> Orioles' Clark Misses Another Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- Will Clark missed a fifth straight start with a  
swollen left knee Tuesday, and there's no telling when he'll be 
back in the Baltimore Orioles' lineup at first base. 
</P>
<P>
	Clark last started July 1 in Toronto. He made a pinch-hitting  
appearance the following day against the New York Yankees, then 
returned to Baltimore on Saturday to have his knee examined. 
</P>
<P>
	He would not comment on his condition Tuesday before limping  
onto the field for warmups. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's the infamous day-to-day,'' manager Ray Miller said. ``He  
got it injected, but he's still a little sore.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Clark is hitting .295 with six homers. Jeff Conine started at  
first base Tuesday night against the Toronto Blue Jays. 
</P>
<P>
 *Notes:* The Orioles donned their 1970s caps Tuesday night -- the  
ones with the cartoon bird centered on a white front panel -- in a 
salute to the past. Between innings of Tuesday night's game, 70s 
music was played over the public address system. Baltimore is 
expected to wear the hats through the homestand that ends Thursday. 
... The Orioles signed draft pick Josh Cenate, a left-handed 
pitcher who went 13-1 with a 0.71 ERA in 15 appearances this spring 
at Jefferson High in West Virginia. Cenate, the Orioles' fifth pick 
and the 34th taken overall, had 179 strikeouts and only 21 walks in 
89 innings this season. He was 34-4 in four seasons. He is 
scheduled to report to the Bluefield Orioles of the Appalachian 
League on Wednesday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
