</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Mark McGwire and Sammy Sosa, who led baseball's  
resurgence with their home-run race last summer, will be starting 
together in the All-Star game for the first time. Arizona second 
baseman Jay Bell overtook Craig Biggio and joined Diamondbacks 
third baseman Matt Williams in the National League's starting 
lineup for next week's All-Star game. Mike Piazza of the New York 
Mets will be at catcher and Barry Larkin of Cincinnati at 
shortstop. 


</P>
