<HEADLINE> Fruit Warehouse Explodes in L.A. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- An explosion and fire destroyed a fruit  
warehouse downtown Tuesday, killing one person and injuring five 
others. 
</P>
<P>
	Deputy Fire Chief Bob Neamy said the cause of the blast was  
under investigation. The business used a flammable ripening agent 
on bananas and other fruit, but there were also reports of a 
propane leak, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The blast happened just before 11 a.m., and firefighters battled  
the flames for more than an hour, pouring water through the 
collapsed roof. 
</P>
<P>
	The unidentified dead person was found in the burned building.  
One victim was hospitalized with serious burns. 
</P>
<P>
	The busiest time in the produce district is in the early morning  
hours. Most work is typically wrapped up by late morning. 
  	   	
</P>
