<HEADLINE> Giants' Bonds Out With Groin Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- San Francisco's Barry Bonds pulled up while  
running out a grounder and left Tuesday night's game against San 
Diego because of tightness in his right groin. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonds began limping about halfway down the line, and, after  
touching first, clutched his groin in obvious pain. He was easily 
thrown out by second baseman Quilvio Veras. 
</P>
<P>
