<HEADLINE> Stars Sign Lind, Sloan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- The Dallas Stars have signed left wing Juha Lind  
to a two-year contract and right wing Blake Sloan to a one-year 
deal. No terms were announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Lind, 25, was the Stars' rookie of the year in 1997-98 after  
totaling two goals and three assists in 39 games. Last year, he 
played with Jokerit Helsinki in the Finnish Elite Hockey League, 
scoring 20 goals with 19 assists. 
</P>
<P>
	Sloan, 24, began last season with the Houston Aeros. He scored  
eight goals with 10 assists in 62 games with Houston, mostly as a 
defenseman. The Stars signed him on March 10, and he played in 14 
regular-season games and 19 of 23 playoff games, including all six 
in the Stanley Cup Finals. 
  	   	
</P>
