<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tiger Woods Improvises in Commercial  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Tiger Woods was killing time, doing trick moves  
with a golf ball during the making of a Nike commercial last month. 
The result: an entirely different ad that will surely add to his 
legend. 
</P>
<P>
	As originally conceived, the ad was to have featured Woods and a  
dozen or so people swinging in sequence at a driving range in 
Orlando, Fla. But Woods had other ideas. 
</P>
<P>
	``These people were dying in the heat out there,'' he said. ``I  
said, `You know what? I'm just going to try to entertain them.' So, 
I went over there and just started juggling the ball and doing 
weird stuff, and they were entertained.'' 
</P>
<P>
	So was the director. Woods was captured on tape bouncing the  
ball off his wedge for 28 seconds, then taking a full swing as the 
ball was in the air. He made tremendous contact. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's really not as hard as you might think if you grew up  
playing baseball,'' Woods said. ``Hand-to-eye coordination -- same 
principle.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
