<HEADLINE> Ventura Signs SLA Extradition Form </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) -- Gov. Jesse Ventura signed an extradition  
warrant Tuesday for Kathleen Soliah, a former member of a radical 
group accused of planting bombs under two Los Angeles police cars 
in 1975. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Soliah, 52, is charged with murder conspiracy and could face  
life in prison if convicted for her alleged role with the 
Symbionese Liberation Army. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities say Ms. Soliah spent 23 years as a fugitive and  
lived under the assumed name of Sarah Jane Olson in the Twin 
Cities. She was married and an active member of her community. 
</P>
<P>
	Her attorney, Howard Bass, has not publicly conceded that Ms.  
Olson is Ms. Soliah. The FBI says fingerprint records prove that 
she is. One issue at an extradition hearing scheduled for July 15 
will be whether Ms. Soliah is who police say she is. 
  	   	
</P>
