<HEADLINE> London Stocks Close at New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- London's Stock Exchange reached a new closing high  
today as European bourses elsewhere fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The Financial Times Stock Exchange-100 index closed up 0.4  
percent at a new record of 6,620.6. London's provisional volume for 
the whole market was 960 million shares. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts said that London share prices were pushed higher by  
U.S. investors on Wall Street bidding technology shares up. 
</P>
<P>
	Automotive stocks in Frankfurt also had a good day. As  
exporters, they benefited from a weakening euro and from an influx 
of foreign investors in search of cheap euro-denominated stocks at 
midday. 
</P>
<P>
	Chemical stocks extended gains but were unable to lift other  
European bourses Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index closed down 0.2 percent. The Paris  
CAC 40 index ended 0.1 percent lower, and Madrid's IBEX-35 index 
was down 0.8 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 594 European companies closed down  
0.85 points, or 0.3 percent, while the Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, 
which tracks 295 companies in countries that joined the euro single 
currency, finished down 0.33 points at 336.53. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index ended down 2.85 points at  
3968.99, while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index was down 10.08 points at 
3934.64. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
