<DOCNO> APW19990706.0185 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-06 14:30:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Stocks End Lower; Dow Down 4.12  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks turned lower in late trading today as  
optimism about second-quarter earnings gave way to selling by 
investors eager to reap gains from last week's stunning gains. The 
Dow Jones industrial average closed down 4.12 at 11,135.12. Earlier 
in the session, the blue-chip index had risen 97.52 points above 
Friday's record close of 11,139.24. Broader stock indicators were 
also lower after a late selloff. The Nasdaq composite index fell 
4.24 to 2,736.78. Stocks faltered as weakness in the bond market 
and a desire to lock in profits outweighed the strong outlook for 
second-quarter profits. 

</P>
