Internet healthcare network led by former Surgeon General Dr. C. 
Everett Koop agreed to pay $89 million to cement an alliance with 
America Online Inc., the dominant provider of Internet access. The 
four-year agreement gives AOL a market to promote a widely 
respected name in medicine and an option to buy stock in the new 
public company drkoop.com. It gives Koop and his company a chance 
