	Gold Prices Fall on British Auction  
</P>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Gold prices on both cash and futures markets  
tumbled today to 20-year lows after Britain kicked off the first in 
a series of auctions that will eventually lead to the sale of more 
than half its reserves. The move, previously announced in May, is 
the latest in a series of high-profile central bank sales that come 
as gold loses its luster in favor of better-returning investments. 
Gold for August delivery fell $6.80 to $257.80 an ounce on the New 
York Mercantile Exchange. Spot gold prices in Europe hit a 20-year 
low at $255.75 a troy ounce. In London, the gold price closed at 
$256.10. 

