ordered Michael Wise to repay the money he stole. Wise pleaded 
guilty to two violations of the federal wire-fraud law for his 
schemes that cost the Aspen-based Cornerstone Private Capital Corp. 
more than $8.7 million. Wise headed Silverado Banking savings and 
loan when it failed in 1988 and was acquitted of charges then. 

