Coca-Cola in Poland posed no threat of food poisoning. While 
declaring the mold and bacteria nonhazardous, officials from the 
provincial Sanepid laboratory said the tested samples of Coca-Cola 
products were below sanitary standards, the official PAP news 
agency reported. The findings matched test results previously 
announced by Coca-Cola and a Dutch laboratory. No illness from 
drinking Coca-Cola products has been reported in Poland. 

