company that has voiced its opposition to the deal. The government, 
which gave the green light for the $43 billion takeover bid late 
yesterday, said today it favored the TotalFina offer because it 
would protect the companies from a U.S. or British acquisition. 
Elf's management was meeting its banking advisers today to prepare 
a response to the unsolicited takeover offer before presenting it 
to its board of directors. The company remained silent about 
whether it planned to fight the bid, designed to create the world's 
fourth largest oil company. 

