daily Reforma reported today. The bank bailout, proposed by 
President Ernesto Zedillo last year, became one of the most 
controversial issues in Mexico before being approved by Congress in 
December 1998. Many lawmakers warned its final cost could well 
exceed government estimates. The Finance Ministry had no immediate 
comment on the report. 

