<HEADLINE> Dodgers' Cromer on 15-Day DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Los Angeles Dodgers infielder Tripp Cromer has an  
irregular heart beat and was put on the 15-day disabled list 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Cromer, 31, was sent back to Los Angeles for testing and  
evaluation by Dr. Michael Mellman. Cromer was hitting .208 with two 
home runs and eight RBIs in 29 games. 
</P>
<P>
	``We won't know anything more until the tests are performed,''  
Los Angeles manager Davey Johnson said before Tuesday's game with 
the Colorado Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
	He is the second player within a week to be diagnosed with an  
irregular heart beat. New York Yankees left fielder Shane Spencer 
was hospitalized during the weekend with a similar problem. 
</P>
<P>
	Los Angeles filled Cromer's spot by activating shortstop Mark  
Grudzielanek, who missed 28 games because of a fractured right 
hand. Grudzielanek was 4-for-16 during a four-game rehabilitation 
assignment at Class-A San Bernardino. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're fortunate to get Mark back with when we did,'' Johnson  
said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
