<DOCNO> APW19990706.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-06 17:20:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Braves' Lopez Hopes To Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- After a series of running drills Tuesday, Atlanta  
Braves catcher Javy Lopez said he hopes to return to the starting 
lineup after next week's All-Star break. 
</P>
<P>
	Lopez, on the disabled list since June 23 with a sprained right  
knee, was eligible to be activated Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	After an MRI last week revealed a slightly torn ligament, the  
two-time All-Star feared he might need reconstructive surgery, 
which would end his season. 
</P>
<P>
	``At least I think I'm coming back now,'' Lopez said.  
</P>
<P>
	Under the watch of assistant trainer Jeff Porter, Lopez wore a  
knee brace as he ran a series of figure eights, quick starts and 
stops on the outfield grass at Turner Field. Lopez said he felt a 
``little bit'' of discomfort but no significant pain. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's basically nothing,'' he said of the pain. ``I was  
impressed because I thought it was going to hurt. The knee brace 
really helped. I didn't feel any pain.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Lopez has been unable to squat in the catcher's stance while  
wearing the brace for more than a few seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	``I would like to go out there and play, not 100 percent  
healthy, but close to it,'' Lopez said. ``I don't want to go now 
and the next day hurt myself again. I want to make sure I can 
play.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Lopez is hitting .321 this season with 11 homers and 37 RBIs. He  
hurt his knee June 20 at Arizona as he slid into second base. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
