<HEADLINE> Rangers' Gunderson To Have Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Texas Rangers left-hander Eric Gunderson  
will undergo surgery on a small tear in his left shoulder on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Gunderson has been on the disabled list since May 8. He made  
five rehabilitation appearances with Triple-A Oklahoma, allowing 
six runs and 11 hits in 6 2-3 innings, and continued to experience 
shoulder problems. 
</P>
<P>
	Gunderson was 0-0 with a 7.20 ERA in 11 games for the Rangers  
prior to going on the disabled list. 
</P>
<P>
	The surgery will be performed by Dr. John Conway, one of the  
Rangers' team doctors. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rangers sent rookie outfielder Ruben Mateo to Oklahoma to  
begin a rehab assignment. 
</P>
<P>
	Mateo, on the disabled list since June 23 with a pulled groin,  
batted .182 with a home run and three RBIs in 10 games for Texas. 
  	   	
</P>
