<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Alzheimer's Patient in Murder Rap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAFRANCE, S.C. (AP) -- A 79-year-old man with Alzheimer's disease  
shot and killed a woman who had been taking care of him, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Clarence Elrod was charged Monday with murder. The name of the  
54-year-old victim was not immediately released. 
</P>
<P>
	Elrod claimed to have no memory of the shooting late Sunday,  
sheriff's investigator Don Hodges said. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators said Elrod called 911 after the shooting the woman  
three times, once in the head. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
